summary: Tony knew it was gonna be a good day. He had slept in until 7am which was generous considering he was living with a baby, and he...
body:
Tony knew it was gonna be a good day. He had slept in until 7am which was generous considering he was living with a baby, and he had the whole day off which meant spending it with Morgan and letting Pepper catch a nap or two. The only plan he had was working on Peters web fluid so he had something impressive to show when Peter came over to work on the Iron Spider that afternoon.

At 2 Tony had put Morgan down for her nap, and at 3 Peter came bouncing in with a smile on his face. He was always smiling. While Tony finished up what he was working on Peter told him about the funny joke Ned had told him in chemistry and the awful meatloaf he had for lunch and the weird comment MJ had about his T-shirt.

“Alright kid try this out”

Tony threw him the web fluid and Peter popped it info his glove and webbed a soda can across the room

“I improved the formula so now it’s twice as sticky and lasts about half an hour more”

Peters smile grew. Tony didn’t think that was possible, but it made him smile too.

“Oh awesome! That would have been really helpful on Titan”

Tonys face fell

“what?”

“You know Mr Stark Titan? Thanos? The infinity Gauntlet?…”

Peter kept talking. Tony felt his breathing quicken. His chest felt heavy, like the air turned to led in his body.

“…the snap?..”

With every word Peter’s smile grew bigger and more malicious

“I died! Remember Mr Stark”

“N-no you’re standing right here”

Peter started laughing

“No Mr Stark I died and it was all your fault”

Those words echoed in Tonys head

“Kid stop please”

He found it harder and harder to get his words out. He felt tears running down his cheeks. All of the sudden Peters face was serious he saw tear lines that weren’t there a second ago. Then he heard the words he dreaded.

“I’m sorry”

~

Tony sat up.

He was drenched in sweat. He felt fresh tears on his cheeks. His breathing was shaky and quick. He turned to the only thing that could make this situation even a hair better.

But she wasnt there either.

“Pepper, Peter, Happy”

They were all gone, and the guilt hadn’t left him from the second he saw the dust. He put his head in his hands and allowed himself to sob.

Then he head a vibration coming from his bedside table.

A flip phone

With the name Steve Rogers.

He hesitated but then decided to pick it up.

“Hello?”

His voice was weak and shaky. He hated how it sounded but that wasn’t what was on his mind right now.

“How fast can you get to Wakanda?” The voice on the other side of the phone asked “we can fix this.”
